Oklahoma Capitol Restoration
July 24, 2017 at 3:38 PM ·

One of our construction workers found this note scrawled on a Game and Fish Dept. envelope and rolled up in a bottle underneath the granite stairs leading to the south portico. Dated Sept. 21, 1933, they wanted to leave notice that they were working in the area. Almost 84 years later, we discovered it. If you recognize any of the names on the note, please reach out to us.

Oklahoma Capitol Restoration
July 5, 2017 at 5:55 PM ·

Stone cleaning is a 3-step process. First, it is power washed. Next, a steam cleaning method is employed. Finally, microabrasion cleaning (small glass beads at low pressure) is used. In this video, a worker power washes the stone on the drum base of the dome.

post_text:
The Capitol will host a March 31 public program on the Magna Carta in the Oklahoma House of Representatives Chambers to accompany the Magna Carta: Enduring Legacy 1215-2015 exhibit the Oklahoma Capitol is hosting from March 23 to April 5.

The exhibit, which is also free and open to the public, will run from March 23 to April 5. It tells the story of and commemorates the 800th anniversary the Magna Carta, widely regarded as one of the most important legal documents in the history of democracy.

At a glance: Magna Carta: Enduring Legacy 1215-2015

Public Program: 3 p.m. Tuesday, March 31, House of Representative Chambers (public gallery entrances on fifth floor)

Exhibit: Monday, March 23, to Sunday, April 5, Supreme Court Hallway (second floor)

Location: Oklahoma State Capitol, 2300 N. Lincoln Boulevard, Oklahoma City

For more information, visit: http://content.govdelivery.com/accounts/OKOMES/bulletins/f9510f
